board.com/charts/year-end/2016/hot-rock-songs |title=Hot Rock Songs \u2013 Year-End 2016 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|80\n|}\n\n===Decade-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2000\u20132009)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA)<ref>{{cite web|title=2000sDecadeChartssingles|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/documents/2000sDecadeChartssingles.pdf|website=ARIA|publisher=ARIA|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|71\n|-\n|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|title=Bestenlisten \u2013 00er-Single|url=http://austriancharts.at/00er_single.asp|website=Austrian Charts|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=20 March 2016|language=German}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|31\n|-\n|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|title=Decenniumlijst: 00's|url=http://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/decenniumlijst-00-s|website=Dutch Top 40|publisher=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40|accessdate=20 March 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|title=Hot 100 Songs \u2013 Decade End Charts|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbbiz/charts/decadeendcharts/2009/hot100-songs|website=Billboard|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=20 March 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020173024/http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/decadeendcharts/2009/hot100-songs|archivedate=20 October 2012}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|49\n|}\n\n===All-time charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart\n!Position\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Aller Tijden \u2013 Singles|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/bestall.asp|website=Ultratop|publisher=Ultratop & Hung Medien|accessdate=20 March 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|75\n|-\n|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|title=Nummer 1 Top 40|url=http://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/best-scorende-nummer-1-hits|website=Dutch Top 40|publisher=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40|accessdate=20 March 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|-\n|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|title=Best of All Time \u2013 Singles |url=http://www.swedishcharts.com/bestall.asp |website=Swedish Charts |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=25 March 2016 |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070221151820/http://www.swedishcharts.com/bestall.asp |archivedate=21 February 2007 }}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|44\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|title=Ewige Bestenliste \u2013 Singles|url=http://hitparade.ch/charts/best/singles|website=Hitparade|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=20 March 2016|language=German}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|39\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100-60th-anniversary|title=Billboard Hot 100 60th Anniversary Interactive Chart|work=Billboard|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|352\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|type=single|award=Platinum|relyear=2015|certyear=2016|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Belgium|award=Platinum|type=single|relyear=2015|relmonth=5|certyear=2016|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Canada|certyear=2009|relyear=2008|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|award=Gold|type=single|salesamount=20,000|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Denmark|award=Platinum|salesamount=90,000|type=single|relyear=2015|relmonth=5|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|certyear=2016|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Germany|certyear=2010|relyear=2008|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|award=Gold|type=single|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Italy|certyear=2016|relyear=2015|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|award=Platinum|number=2|type=single|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|type=single|award=Platinum|recent=website|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|id=4211|accessdate=March 25, 2016|certyear=2016|relyear=2015}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Spain|award=Platinum|number=3|type=single|relyear=2015|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|relmonth=5|certyear=2016|id=coldplay-viva-la-vida-2|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Switzerland|type=single|award=Platinum|recent=website|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|id=4211|accessdate=March 25, 2016|certyear=2016|relyear=2015}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|award=Platinum|number=2|salesamount=1,440,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/coldplay-s-official-top-20-biggest-songs-on-the-uks-official-chart__4117/|title=Coldplay's Official Top 20 biggest songs on the UK's Official Chart|last=White|first=Jack|work=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=29 November 2018|accessdate=30 November 2018}}</ref>|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|relyear=2015|certyear=2017||accessdate=30 November 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|award=Platinum|number=3|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|relyear=2015|certyear=2015|accessdate=March 12, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of best-selling singles]]\n* [[List of best-selling singles in the United States]]\n*[[List of Billboard Adult Contemporary number ones of 2009]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|coldplay|viva-la-vida}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n* [http://www.frida-kahlo-foundation.org/Viva-la-Vida,-1954.html Frida Kahlo's \"Viva la Vida\"]\n\n{{Coldplay singles}}\n{{Grammy Award for Song of the Year 2000s}}\n{{Jay Z songs}}\n{{Darin Zanyar}}\n\n[[Category:2008 songs]]\n[[Category:2008 singles]]\n[[Category:Coldplay songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Alternative Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Contemporary number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Anton Corbijn]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Hype Williams]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Parlophone singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Brian Eno]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Jon Hopkins]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Markus Dravs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Rik Simpson]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Chris Martin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jonny Buckland]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Guy Berryman]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Will Champion]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Torch songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs involved in plagiarism controversies]]\n[[Category:Rock ballads]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2008 single by Coldplay}}\n{{About|the Coldplay song|the Coldplay album|Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends||Viva la Vida (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Viva la Vida\n| cover      = Coldplay - Viva la Vida.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Coldplay]]\n| album      = [[Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends]]\n| B-side     = Death Will Never Conquer\n| released   = {{Start date|2008|5|25|df=yes}}\n| format     = {{flatlist|\n* [[CD single|CD]]\n* [[Music download|digital download]]\n}}\n| recorded   = 2007\u20132008\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Baroque pop]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Pop Music, Pop Culture|first=Chris|last=Rojek|publisher=Polity Press|location=Cambridge|year=2011|page=46}}</ref>\n| length     = {{unbulleted list|{{Duration|m=4|s=01}} {{small|(album version)}}|{{Duration|m=3|s=45}} {{small|([[radio edit]])}}}}\n| label      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Parlophone]]\n* [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n}}\n| writer     = {{flatlist|\n* [[Guy Berryman]]\n* [[Jonny Buckland]]\n* [[Will Champion]]\n* [[Chris Martin]]\n}}\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Markus Dravs]]\n* [[Brian Eno]]\n* [[Jon Hopkins]]\n* [[Rik Simpson]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Violet Hill]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Lovers in Japan]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|dvgZkm1xWPE|\"Viva La Vida\"}}<br/>{{YouTube|1kVxpsi1XQ4|\"Viva La Vida\" (Alternative Version)}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Viva La Vida'''\" ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|v|i\u02d0|v|\u0259|_|l|\u0259|_|\u02c8|v|i\u02d0|d|\u0259}}, {{IPA-es|\u02c8bi\u03b2a la \u02c8\u03b2i\u00f0a|lang}}; {{langnf||Spanish| \"Long Live Life\"}}<!-- \u201cla\u201d meaning \u201cthe\u201d is required to accompany the abstract noun \u201cvida\u201d (\u201clife\u201d) in Spanish, but should not be included in an English translation of the phrase.-->) is a song by British [[Rock music|rock]] band [[Coldplay]]. It was written by all members of the band for their fourth album, ''[[Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends|Viva La Vida or Death and All His Friends]]'' (2008), and was released as the second single from the album. On the album, this song segues directly into the next track, \"[[Violet Hill]]\".\n\nThe lyrics to the song contain historical and Christian references, and the track is built around a looping [[string section]] in unison with a digital processed piano, with other layers gradually being added as the song builds.\n\nThe song was released on 13 June 2008 as the album's second single, debuting to critical acclaim and commercial success. \"Viva la Vida\" reached the top spot of the [[UK Singles Chart]] and [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming the band's first number-one single in both the U.S. and U.K. The song won the [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year]] at the [[51st Annual Grammy Awards]] in 2009. The song became the sixth song to reach the 4 million mark in paid downloads in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/41000/week-ending-aug-16-2009-king-of-country-boots-king-of-pop/ |title=Week Ending Aug. 16, 2009: King Of Country Boots King Of Pop \u2013 Chart Watch |publisher=New.music.yahoo.com |accessdate=2010-08-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827082907/http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/41000/week-ending-aug-16-2009-king-of-country-boots-king-of-pop |archivedate=27 August 2009 }}</ref> It has sold over 7.1 million copies worldwide by 2014, and over 6 million in the U.S. alone by June 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-june-23-2013-songs-miley-comeback-202517109.html |title=Week Ending June 23, 2013. Songs: Miley's Comeback Hit |date=2013-06-26 |publisher=Yahoo! |first=Paul |last=Grein |accessdate=2013-06-28 }}\n* {{cite certification|region=Australia|type=single|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|certyear=2008|relyear=2008}}\n* {{cite certification|region=Brazil|type=single|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|certyear=2010|relyear=2008}}\n* {{cite certification|region=Canada|type=single|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida \u2013 Death and All His Friends|certyear=2009|relyear=2008}}\n* {{cite certification|region=Germany|type=single|artist=Coldplay|title=Viva la Vida|certyear=2010|relyear=2008}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/files/listasanuales/canciones/Top%2050%20Canciones%20Anual%202009.pdf |title=TOP 50 CANCIONES ANUAL 2009 (Spanish certifications) |publisher=PROMUSICAE |language=Spanish |accessdate=2010-02-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5qK6BF6vi |archivedate=8 June 2010 }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/will-youngs-evergreen-named-best-selling-single-of-the-21st-century/048820|title=Will Young's Evergreen named best selling single of the 21st century|last=Rhian|first=Jones|magazine=[[Music Week]]|date=2012-05-08|accessdate=2012-07-18}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.buzzjack.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=141954 |title=Top 150 Best Selling singles of the 21st Century, Complete! Full list first post|author=Gezza7T6|publisher=BuzzJack.com|work=[[Music Week]]|date=2012-05-07|accessdate=2012-07-18}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe song's Spanish title, \"Viva la Vida\", is taken from a painting by 20th-century [[Mexico|Mexican]] artist [[Frida Kahlo]]. In Spanish {{lang|es|viva}} is an expression used to acclaim someone or something,<ref name=\"Diccionario de la lengua Espa\u00f1ola\">{{cite web |url= http://lema.rae.es/drae/?val=vivar |accessdate =10 April 2014}}</ref> so \"Long Live Life\" is an accurate translation and the painting reflects the artistic irony of acclaiming life while suffering physically.<ref name=Frida-Kahlo>{{cite web |url= http://www.frida-kahlo-foundation.org/Viva-la-Vida,-1954.html | accessdate=10 April 2014}}</ref> When asked about the album's title, referring to Frida Kahlo's strength, enduring [[polio]], a broken spine, and a decade of chronic pain, lead singer [[Chris Martin]] said: \"She went through a lot of pain, of course, and then she started a big painting in her house that said 'Viva la Vida', I just loved the boldness of it.\"<ref name=rollingstone>{{cite web |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/rolling-stone-exclusive-coldplays-new-album-title-revealed-20080318 |title=Coldplay's New Album Title Revealed; RollingStone |work=rollingstone.com  |accessdate=16 June 2012|date=18 March 2008 }}</ref>\n\nDuring the album's production, \"Viva la Vida\" was one of the songs that had polarised each member's opinion over which version they should choose. In an interview, Martin recalled: \"We did quite a few different versions and went round the houses a bit and eventually settled on those treatments for it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.absoluteradio.co.uk/music/artists/coldplay/article/3345.html|title=Viva La Vida interview: Full transcript|publisher=Absoluteradio.co.uk|accessdate=2008-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090204195406/http://www.absoluteradio.co.uk/music/artists/coldplay/article/3345.html|archive-date=4 February 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n{{Listen\n| filename    = Viva la Vida.ogg\n| title       = \"Viva la Vida\"\n| description = The sample contains the beginning snippet of the song\n| pos = left\n}}\n{{Quote box\n | quote = \"'Viva La Vida' soars in with a grandiose instrumental arrangement and sweeping lyrics detailing the pain of being deposed from a lofty position. The big sound of the song constantly verges on becoming overblown, but Coldplay knows how to walk the tightrope perfectly. Bells and chimes and orchestral swells are all there on the chorus, but Chris Martin's voice still pierces through like a clarion call. Lyrically, the pain of the protagonist is clear, but the sweep of words about Jerusalem bells, Roman Calvary choirs, and Saint Peter give 'Viva La Vida' an air of intelligence rare in today's most popular pop songs.\"\n | source = \u2014Bill Lamb, ''About.com''.<ref>[http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/vivalavida.htm Coldplay \u2013 \"Viva La Vida\" \u2013 Review of the single \"Viva La Vida\" by pop-rock band Coldplay | By Bill Lamb, About.com.]</ref>\n | width = 25em\n | align = right\n}}\n[[File:Will Champion - Viva la Vida tour.jpg|thumb|right|Will Champion with the [[Timpani|timpano]] and [[church bell]] used in the song]]\nThe lyrics to \"Viva la Vida\" are narrated by a protagonist who says he \"used to rule the world\". Martin has explained the song lyric \"I know [[Saint Peter]] won't call my name\" in an interview with ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]'' magazine: \"It's about&nbsp;... You're not on the list.\"<ref>{{cite news|first=Ian|last=Youngs|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/7439967.stm|title=Joining Coldplay's musical journey|accessdate=2008-06-25|date=2008-06-06|publisher=BBC}}</ref> When asked about the song, bass guitarist [[Guy Berryman]] said: \"It's a story about a king who's lost his kingdom, and all the album's artwork is based on the idea of revolutionaries and [[guerrillas]]. There's this slightly anti-authoritarian viewpoint that's crept into some of the lyrics and it's some of the pay-off between being surrounded by governments on one side, but also we're human beings with emotions and we're all going to die and the stupidity of what we have to put up with every day. Hence the album title.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.q4music.com/2008/05/coldplay_viva_la_vida_2.html|title=Coldplay: Viva La Vida|accessdate=2008-06-01|work=The Q Daily}}</ref>\n\nUnlike the then-typical arrangement of Coldplay songs, in which either the guitar or [[piano]] is the prominent instrument, the track mostly consists of a [[string section]] and a digital piano playing the song's upbeat riff, along with a steady bass drum beat, percussion (including a [[Timpani|timpano]] and a [[church bell]]), bass guitar, and Martin's vocals; there is limited use of electric guitar. All the strings are arranged and conducted by violinist [[Davide Rossi]], who is one of the main collaborators of the album. Rossi's strings comprise the main driving force throughout the song, with a strong beginning loop that supports Martin's voice, until the choruses where the symphonic power of the orchestra takes its fullest shape. The prominent chords played by the string section throughout the song (and in the chorus of \"Rainy Day,\" another of the band's songs) are very similar to those used by \"Viva la Vida\" co-producer Brian Eno in his piece \"An Ending (Ascent),\" meaning they could have been suggested partially for the song by Eno.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=[[Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends]]|others=[[Coldplay]]|year=2008|publisher=[[EMI]]|location=United Kingdom}}</ref>\n\nThe song is written in the key of [[A-flat major]]. Its main chord progression is D\u266d/E\u266d/A\u266d/Fm. Time signature is 4/4 and the ''tempo'' is 138.\n\n==Release and promotion==\n\n\"Viva la Vida\" was initially released only with [[iTunes Store]] pre-orders of ''Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends'' on 7 May 2008&nbsp;\u2013 the \"new edit\" version of the song&nbsp;\u2013 which led to the song's temporary exclusion from the UK Singles Chart.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jsonline.com/entertainment/musicandnightlife/29511564.html|title=CD Spotlight|last=M.|first=Jon|date=2008-06-20|work=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]]|accessdate=2008-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081228182826/http://www.jsonline.com/entertainment/musicandnightlife/29511564.html|archive-date=28 December 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was released as a download-only single on 25 May 2008, and a physical CD single in Europe on 29 July 2008 to coincide with the release of the single's music videos. \"Viva la Vida\" was well-downloaded in the internet, becoming iTunes' best-selling song of 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/12/02/coldplay-leona-lewis-top-itunes-2008-sales-chart/|title=Coldplay, Leona Lewis Top iTunes 2008 Sales Chart|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=2008-12-02|work=Rolling Stone|accessdate=2008-12-10}}</ref>\n\nThe song was used as part of [[Apple Inc.]]'s [[iPod advertising|iPod + iTunes advertisement campaign]].<ref name=\"ew review\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/ent/music/cdreviews/5840926.html|title=Coldplay channels U2 on new album|last=Guerra|first=Joey|date=2008-06-16|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|accessdate=2008-11-12}}</ref> Coldplay performed the song live for the first time at the [[2008 MTV Movie Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/06/02/mtv-movie-awards-reunites-wayne-and-garth-honors-transformers/|title=MTV Movie Awards Reunites Wayne and Garth, Features First TV Performance of New Coldplay Single|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=2008-06-02|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=2008-11-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/wires/2008Jun01/0,4670,MTVMovieAwards,00.html|title=Over-the-top MTV Movie Awards have smoke, no fire|last=Lang|first=Derrick J.|date=2008-06-01|publisher=[[Fox News Channel]]|accessdate=2008-11-12}}</ref> It has since gone on to make many media appearances, including being featured throughout the episode [[List of Medium episodes#Season 5: 2009|\"A Person of Interest\"]] from the [[paranormal]] drama ''[[Medium (TV Series)|Medium]]'', as a song played on the radio in the episode \"We're Not in Kansas Anymore\" from the teen drama ''[[90210 (TV series)|90210]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2008/09/03/90210-premiere-how-does-it-compare-to-the-old-bev/|title='90210\u2032 Premiere: How Does It Compare To The Old Bev?|last=Stolz|first=Kim |date=2008-09-03|publisher=MTV|accessdate=2008-11-12}}</ref> used as [[bumper music]] on [[William Bennett|Bill Bennett]]'s \"Morning in America\" radio talk show, and on the international soundtrack to the Brazilian soap opera ''[[A Favorita]]'' which helped push \"Viva la Vida\" up the charts in Brazil, where the telenovela had been shown.<ref name=\"Som Livre\">{{cite web | last = | first =  | url =http://www.somlivre.com/?1430/produto/CD/A-favorita-Internacional/Varios---A-Favorita\n | title =A Favorita Soundtrack  | publisher = A Favorita International Soundtrack | month= | year=2008 }}</ref> In 2009, [[Solange Knowles]] covered the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/promo-42778155-53-20090127-autoplay |title=Pepsi Music |publisher=Music.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=2010-08-29}}</ref> [[Lady Gaga]] also covered the song for [[BBC Radio 1]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8uFRg2epy-w |title=Broadcast Yourself |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2010-08-29}}</ref> A live version of the song appeared on Coldplay's 2009 [[live album]] ''[[LeftRightLeftRightLeft]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2009/05/01/coldplay-reward-fans-with-free-live-lp-leftrightleftrightleft/|title=Coldplay Reward Fans With Free Live LP \"LeftRightLeftRightLeft\"|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=2009-05-01|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=2009-05-21}}</ref>\nIt was also used in an episode entitled \"[[Million Dollar Maybe]]\" of ''[[The Simpsons]]''. The song was covered in the [[The X Factor (UK series 7)|seventh series]] of ''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]'' by the boyband [[One Direction]] in 2010.\n\n==Music videos==\nThe official music video for \"Viva La Vida\" was directed by [[Hype Williams]] and premiered at Coldplay's official website on 1 August 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coldplay.com/vivavideo1.php|title=Viva la Vida video 1|accessdate=2008-08-01|publisher=Coldplay.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080805011305/http://www.coldplay.com/vivavideo1.php|archive-date=5 August 2008|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The video depicts the band performing against a blurry, warped version of [[Eug\u00e8ne Delacroix]]'s painting ''[[Liberty Leading the People|La Libert\u00e9 guidant le peuple]]'', ending with the band members crumbling into rose petals. The video currently has 605 million views on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Citation|last=Coldplay Official|title=Coldplay \u2013 Viva La Vida|date=2008-08-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dvgZkm1xWPE|accessdate=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Coldplay - Viva La Vida Official Alternate Screenshot.jpg|thumb|right|Chris Martin as the king in the [[Anton Corbijn]] video]]\nA second, alternate video was shot in [[The Hague]], the Netherlands, directed by [[Anton Corbijn]] and released alongside the first.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coldplay.com/vivavideo2.php|title=Viva la Vida video 2|accessdate=2008-11-11|publisher=Coldplay.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081116040924/http://www.coldplay.com/vivavideo2.php|archive-date=16 November 2008|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> This second version is a tribute to Corbijn's video for [[Depeche Mode]]'s \"[[Enjoy the Silence]]\" and portrays Chris Martin as the king from whose perspective the song is sung. During the video, he carries Delacroix's painting. At the end, he hangs the picture up in a white stall on top of a hill. As he sings the last chorus, his bandmates surface heading his way, tying in loose ends from the \"[[Violet Hill (song)|Violet Hill]]\" video.\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"Viva La Vida\" received widespread critical acclaim. In the ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' review of the album, critic Chris Willman wrote: \"Take the title track&nbsp;... on which [Martin] imagines himself as a paranoid monarch. 'Who would ever want to be king?' Martin asks. 'Revolutionaries wait/For my head on a silver plate!' The confident majesty of the music, however, belies how he and his bandmates <!--{{sic}}--> have invigorated their rock-lite reign.\"<ref name=\"ew review\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20206310,00.html|title=Viva La Vida \u2013 Music Review|last=Willman|first=Chris|date=2008-06-13|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=2008-11-11}}</ref> Josh Hathaway from ''[[The Plain Dealer]]'' noted \"Viva la Vida\" as the \"catchiest\" song on the album.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blog.cleveland.com/musicreviews/2008/07/music_review_coldplay_viva_la.html|title=Coldplay \u2013 Viva La Vida \u2013 Music Reviews|last=Hathaway|first=Josh|date=2008-07-15|work=[[The Plain Dealer]]|accessdate=2008-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203194302/http://blog.cleveland.com/musicreviews/2008/07/music_review_coldplay_viva_la.html|archive-date=3 February 2009|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Chris Jones of the [[BBC]] noted: \"The string/brass mutations that bolster a track like 'Viva La Vida'&nbsp;... conjure tunes so sweetly melancholy.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/release/2h54/|title=Coldplay \u2013 Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends|last=Jones|first=Chris|date=2008-06-12|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2008-11-11}}</ref> In the [[IGN]] review, critic Chad Grischow wrote, \"It is their one and only foray into unabashed orchestral pop, but the punchy strut of the strings and fantastic marching vocals make it far too charming and lively to dislike, and even harder not to love.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.ign.com/articles/883/883028p1.html|title=IGN: Viva La Vida Review|last=Grischow|first=Chad|date=2008-06-19|website=IGN|accessdate=2008-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090101021740/http://music.ign.com/articles/883/883028p1.html|archive-date=1 January 2009|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Will Champion - Viva la Vida.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Champion performing \"Viva la Vida\" during the [[Viva la Vida Tour]]]]\n\"Viva la Vida\" was nominated for \"[[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]]\", and won \"[[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]\", and \"[[Grammy Award for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocal|Best Pop Performance by a Duo or a Group]]\" at the [[2009 Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1600678/20081204/coldplay.jhtml|title=Lil Wayne, Coldplay Lead Grammy Nominations|last=Harris|first=Chris|date=2008-12-04|publisher=MTV|accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1604545/20090208/story.jhtml|title=Grammy 2009 Winners List|author=MTV News Staff|date=2009-02-08|publisher=MTV|accessdate=2009-02-21}}</ref> This song also won the [[Ivor Novello Award]] for \"Best Selling British Single\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theivors.com/winners.htm |title=Nominations for the Ivor Novello Awards |publisher=Theivors.com |date=2010-05-20 |accessdate=2010-08-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090424060523/http://www.theivors.com/winners.htm |archivedate=24 April 2009 }}</ref> The song was included in ''[[Rolling Stone]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s annual \"100 Best Songs\" of 2008 at number nine;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/news/story/24947047/the_100_best_singles_of_2008/3|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2008|accessdate=2008-12-25|date=2008-12-25|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|page=3}}</ref> it was also voted number two on ''Rolling Stone''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Readers' Rock List: Best Songs of 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2008/12/22/readers-rock-list-best-songs-of-2008/|title=Readers Rock List Best Songs of 2008|accessdate=2009-03-20|date=2008-12-22|work=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref> \"Viva la Vida\" was also listed at number five on ''Blender''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s 1001 Downloads: The Top 144 Songs of 2008,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.blender.co/articles/default.aspx?key=45697&pg=9|title=The Top 144 Songs of 2008|accessdate=2009-03-20|work=[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]|page=9}}</ref> as well in the number eight position on ''Village Voice''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Pazz and Jop list.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/pazznjop/singles/2008/|title=Pazz and Jop list|accessdate=2009-03-20|work=[[The Village Voice]]}}</ref> According to [[Acclaimed Music]], it is the 455th most celebrated song in popular music history, and the 2nd best song of 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.acclaimedmusic.net/song/S4706.htm|title=Viva La Vida ranked 455th most celebrated song|work=Acclaimed Music|access-date=15 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n\"Viva la Vida\" has been sampled in several other songs, including [[Flo Rida]]'s single \"[[Be on You]]\", [[Mac Miller]]'s \"Cut the Check\" featuring [[Chief Keef]] (from his [[GO:OD AM]] album) and [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]'s \"Congratulations\" from his [[So Far Gone (mixtape)|So Far Gone]] mixtape.\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Viva la Vida\" has become the band's highest charting single. Fueled by high digital sales, the song peaked at the top spot of the U.S. [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming the band's first and, to date, only US number-one single and their second top ten on the Hot 100.<ref name=\"CaulfieldHeaded\">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045040/coldplay-headed-to-no-1-on-billboard-200-hot-100 |title=Coldplay Headed To No. 1 On Billboard 200, Hot 100 |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=2008-06-18 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=2009-01-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140625095349/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045040/coldplay-headed-to-no-1-on-billboard-200-hot-100 |archivedate=25 June 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"CohenDrive\">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045034/digital-sales-drive-coldplay-to-top-of-hot-100 |title=Digital Sales Drive Coldplay To Top Of Hot 100 |last=Cohen |first=Jonathan |date=2008-06-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=2009-01-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628102709/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045034/digital-sales-drive-coldplay-to-top-of-hot-100 |archivedate=28 June 2014 }}</ref> It is the first song by a British group to reach number-one on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 since \"[[Wannabe (song)|Wannabe]]\" by the [[Spice Girls]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|first=James|last=Masterson|url=http://new.uk.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chartwatch/262/week-ending-june-28th-2008/|title=Chart Watch \u2013 Week Ending 28 June 2008|accessdate=2008-08-29|date=2008-06-22|publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]]}}</ref> Although the song was initially successful in digital sales,<ref name=\"CaulfieldHeaded\" /><ref name=\"CohenDrive\" /> after being released, it went on to become the band's highest-charting single in American radio, becoming their first top-ten hit on the [[Hot 100 Airplay]] where it peaked at number eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2009-01-03/radio-songs |title=Hot 100 Airplay: Viva la Vida |year=2009 |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=2009-01-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628095653/http://www.billboard.com/charts/2009-01-03/radio-songs |archivedate=28 June 2014 }}</ref> It had also become the band's first number-one single on the ''Billboard'' [[Alternative Songs|Modern Rock Tracks]] chart.<ref name=\"chart history\">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=coldplay|chart=all}}|title= Artist Chart History \u2013 Coldplay|accessdate=2008-09-02|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc}}</ref>  On the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Adult Top 40 Tracks]], the song has become the band's first number one, as well as the first single on the [[Capitol Records]] label to ever top the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/chart_beat/bonus.jsp|title=''Billboard'' Chart Beat|accessdate=2008-11-11|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> The single has been certified triple platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?resultpage=1&table=SEARCH_RESULTS&title=viva%20la%20vida&format=SINGLE&sort=Artist&perPage=25|title=Gold & Platinum: Search Results|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=28 March 2009}}</ref> The song also became one of the first six songs to reach the 4 million mark in paid digital downloads. As of January 2014, it had sold 6,131,000 units in the US.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/music-news/chart-watch-radioactive-sets-rock-record-001439867.html |title=Can You Believe \"Don't Stop Believin'\" Loses Spot as Best-Selling Rock Song? |author=Paul Grein |work=Chart Watch |publisher=Yahoo |date=2 January 2014 }}</ref>\n\nThe single was also successful in the United Kingdom. Although the song had been disqualified from the UK charts due to initially being available only by pre-ordering the album on [[iTunes]], it became eligible to chart after the album was released. \"Viva la Vida\" hit number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]], becoming Coldplay's first chart-topping single in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045007/coldplay-dominates-uk-album-singles-charts |title=Coldplay Dominates U.K. Album, Singles Charts |last=Sexton |first=Paul |date=2008-06-23 |work=Billboard |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |accessdate=2008-12-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140624002122/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1045007/coldplay-dominates-uk-album-singles-charts |archivedate=24 June 2014 }}</ref>\n\nIn Canada, the single made a \"Hot Shot Debut\" at number four on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] on the issue of 24 May, making it Coldplay's highest debut there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2008-05-24/canadian-hot-100 |title=Canadian Hot 100 |accessdate=2008-01-22 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621020201/http://www.billboard.com/charts/2008-05-24/canadian-hot-100 |archivedate=21 June 2013 }}</ref> It is also one of Coldplay's three highest-charting singles in [[Australia]], reaching number two (both \"[[A Sky Full of Stars]]\" and \"[[Something Just Like This]]\" matched this peak in 2014 and 2017, respectively). In [[New Zealand]], the song was less successful, only peaking at number 16; however, the song stayed in the top 40 for 27 non-consecutive weeks.\n\nIn Spain, the single peaked at #2 and achieved Double Platinum status due to the 80,000 copies sold. It also had a strong airplay on the Spanish radio stations.\n\n===Sporting usage===\n{{more citations needed section|date=February 2013}}\n[[File:Chris-Martin-BBC-live.jpg|thumb|Martin performing \"Viva la Vida\" during the band's 2008 [[Viva la Vida Tour]]]]\nDuring the 2008\u201309 season, the German football club [[Hamburger SV]] used \"Viva la Vida\" as their goal celebration song.\nIt's also the goal celebration song of the German football club [[Hannover 96]].\nThe song also became the anthem of Spanish football club [[FC Barcelona]] during the [[2008\u201309 FC Barcelona season|2008\u201309 season]]. It turned out to be a season of unprecedented success for the Spanish club in 2009, as they won all six competitions they could possibly be involved in, which no football club has managed before in history. The song was selected by the manager of the club, [[Pep Guardiola]] \u2013 himself a Coldplay fan \u2013 to help motivate and encourage his team. It was often played at the [[Camp Nou]] before the start of a Barcelona match. The song was also played during Pep Guardiola's farewell before his final match coaching Barcelona at the Nou Camp, a 4\u20130 victory against Espanyol on 5 May 2012.\n[[UEFA]] used \"Viva la Vida\" as the goal celebration song for the [[2012 UEFA Champions League Final]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Luckhurst|first=Samuel|title=Chelsea Beat Bayern Munich In Champions League Final On Penalties (GALLERY)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/05/19/bayern-munich-champions-league-final-2012_n_1529815.html|work=Huffington Post|accessdate=15 February 2013|date=19 May 2012}}</ref> and [[2012 UEFA Europa League Final|Europa League Final]].\n\nThe [[National Hockey League]]'s [[New York Rangers]] played \"Viva la Vida\" at [[Madison Square Garden]] after victories during the 2011 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=New York Rangers -- Sounds of the Game|url=http://rangers.nhl.com/club/page.htm?id=68601|publisher=nhl.com|accessdate=15 February 2013}}</ref>\nThe song was used by the [[Vancouver Canucks]] in a tribute video during [[Markus N\u00e4slund|Markus N\u00e4slund's]] number retirement ceremony held in [[Vancouver]]'s [[Rogers Arena]]. It was also used in Game 7 of the [[2011 Stanley Cup Finals]] when the [[Boston Bruins]] won the Stanley Cup on Vancouver Ice.\nThe [[Kansas City Chiefs]] play the song at the end of home games in [[Arrowhead Stadium]]. Additionally, it is also used by the [[Kansas City Royals]] to celebrate home runs and wins at [[Kauffman Stadium]].\nThis was the at-bat music of [[Scott Rolen]], former [[third baseman]] of the [[Cincinnati Reds]].\nThe song was also used pre-match during every [[2008 Rugby League World Cup]] game before the two teams took to the field and in the [[halftime show]] of [[Super Bowl 50]] in 2016.\n\n===Plagiarism allegations===\nColdplay were first accused of [[Musical plagiarism|plagiarism]] of \"The Songs I Didn't Write\" by American alternative band Creaky Boards, for the melody of \"Viva la Vida\".<ref>{{cite news|first=Guy|last=Adams|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/the-song-they-didnt-write-coldplay-are-accused-of-plagiarism-by-american-band-849992.html|title=The song they didn't write? Coldplay are accused of plagiarism by American band|accessdate=2008-11-11|date=2008-06-19|work=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> Creaky Boards' band member Andrew Hoepfner claimed that Martin had heard them playing the song at a live show in October 2007.<ref name=\"NMECopied\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/coldplay/37396|title=Coldplay: ''Viva La Vida' not copied from Brooklyn band''|date=2008-06-16|work=NME|accessdate=2008-12-05}}</ref> The band released a video clip, in which it compares sections of both songs.<ref name=\"NMECopied\" /> Coldplay denied the claim. Band spokesman Murray Chambers said Martin was working in [[Associated Independent Recording|AIR Studios]] in London at that time, having checked the singer's diary.<ref name=\"Telegraph\">{{cite news|first=Nicole|last=Martin|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/celebritynews/2163625/Coldplay-didn%27t-copy-us,-says-American-band.html|title=Coldplay didn't copy us, says American band|accessdate=2008-11-11|date=2008-06-20|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]}}</ref> In addition, Coldplay had recorded a [[demo (music)|demo]] version of \"Viva la Vida\" in March 2007, long before Creaky Boards performed it live in October of the same year.<ref name=\"NMECopied\" /> Creaky Boards later retracted the accusations and speculated that both songs may have been inspired by the video game ''[[The Legend of Zelda (video game)|The Legend of Zelda]]''.<ref name=\"Telegraph\" />\n\nOn December 4, 2008, American guitarist [[Joe Satriani]] filed a copyright infringement suit against Coldplay in Los Angeles.<ref name=\"musicradar\">{{cite web |url=http://www.musicradar.com/news/guitars/joe-satriani-sues-coldplay-185735 |title=Joe Satriani sues Coldplay |publisher=[[MusicRadar]]|accessdate=2009-02-13 |date=2008-12-04 |last=Leonard|first=Michael}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dockets.justia.com/docket/california/cacdce/2:2008cv07987/432491|title=Joe Satriani v. Christopher Martin et al|website=Justia Dockets & Filings}}</ref> The suit claims that \"Viva la Vida\" incorporates \"substantial, original portions\" of his instrumental track \"If I Could Fly\" from his 2004 album ''[[Is There Love in Space?]]''<ref>{{cite news|last=Goodman|first=Dan|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/lifestyleMolt/idUKTRE4B40XV20081205|title=Guitarist accuses Coldplay of plagiarism|work=Reuters|date=5 December 2008|accessdate=5 December 2008}}</ref>  The band has denied the allegation, saying the similarities were \"entirely coincidental\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.coldplay.com/newsdetail.php?id=242 |title=Joe Satriani |publisher=Coldplay.com |accessdate=2008-12-10 |date=2008-10-09}}</ref>  On September 14, 2009, the case was dismissed by the [[United States District Court for the Central District of California|California Central District Court]], with both parties potentially agreeing to an out-of-court settlement.<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.nme.com/news/coldplay/47325|title=Coldplay's Joe Satriani lawsuit dismissed from court|magazine=[[NME]]|date=2009-09-15}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2009, [[Yusuf Islam]] stated that the song is very similar to his song \"[[Foreigner (Cat Stevens album)|Foreigner Suite]],\" recorded under his former stage name, [[Cat Stevens]]. He said \"My son brought it to my attention and said: 'Doesn't that sound like 'Foreigner Suite?'\"<ref name=\"Foreigner Suite\">Tourtellotte, Bob (editor). [http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268724/cat-stevens-may-sue-coldplay-it-depends-on-how-well-satriani-does \"Cat Stevens May Sue Coldplay: 'It Depends On How Well Satriani Does'\"]. [[billboard.com]]. May 5th, 2009.</ref> Islam said that any legal action he might take \"depends on how well Satriani does.\"<ref name=\"Foreigner Suite\" /> [[Coldplay]] drummer [[Will Champion]] denied the claim, stating, \"We're confident we haven't done anything wrong.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://hamptonroads.com/2009/05/coldplay-takes-its-music-new-territory |title=Coldplay takes its music into new territory |newspaper=[[The Virginian-Pilot]] |author=Venable, Malcolm|accessdate=2009-05-18 |date=2009-05-18}}</ref>  In June 2009, Islam later said, \"They did copy my song but I don't think they did it on purpose,\" adding, \"I don't want them to think I am angry with them. I'd love to sit down and have a cup of tea with them and let them know it's okay.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/music/international/2009/yusuf-islam-peace-coldplay-150609.html |title=Yusuf Islam wants to make peace Coldplay |publisher=[[Oneindia.in]] |accessdate=2009-06-16 |date=2009-06-15}}</ref>\n\nIn a documentary for [[Sveriges Television]] (2011) American music professor Dr. Lawrence Ferrara showed that the melody structures of \"Viva La Vida\", \"If I Could Fly\" and \"Foreigner Suite\" were very similar to the composition \"[[Se tu m'ami]]\" by the Italian composer [[Giovanni Battista Pergolesi]], who died in 1736. \"Obviously this is a work that we would call in the 'public domain'\", Dr. Ferrara said.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://svtplay.se/v/2659819/hitlatens_historia/coldplay_-_viva_la_vida |title=Coldplay \u2013 Viva la Vida \u2013 Hitl\u00e5tens historia episode 1, 20:38 \u2013 23:34 |publisher=SVT Play |date=2011-12-27 |accessdate=2012-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110160526/http://svtplay.se/v/2659819/hitlatens_historia/coldplay_-_viva_la_vida |archive-date=10 January 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nChris Martin once said that the plagiarism allegations were inspiring him and added: \"If everyone's trying to take away our best song, then we'd better write 25 better ones!\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2009/05/coldplays-chris-martin-inspired-by-plagiarism-lawsuit/ |title=Coldplay's Chris Martin \"Inspired\" By Plagiarism Lawsuit|date=22 May 2009}}</ref> Will Champion has also talked about the accusation saying, \"For some reason, God only knows why, the successful songs seem to be the ones that are accused of being stolen.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicradar.com/news/guitars/coldplays-will-champion-baffled-by-plagiarism-claims-206507|title=Coldplay's Will Champion baffled by plagiarism claims|first=Joe|last=Bosso 2009-05-11T14:34:00.13Z|website=MusicRadar}}</ref>\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download\n| title1   = Viva la Vida\n| length1  = 4:04\n| note1    = New edit\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = CD single\n| title1   = Viva la Vida\n| length1  = 4:01\n| note1    = \n| title2   = Death Will Never Conquer\n| length2  = 1:18\n| note2    = \n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Promotional CD single\n| title1   = Viva la Vida\n| length1  = 3:45\n| note1    = Radio edit\n| title2   = Viva la Vida\n| length2  = 4:01\n| note2    = Album version\n}}\n\n==Live version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = [[Lost!|Lost+]] / Viva la Vida (Live at the 51st Annual Grammy Awards)\n| cover      = Lost? (+Jay-Z) - Viva La Vida (Live At the 51st Annual Grammy Awards).jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Coldplay]] with [[Jay-Z]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{Start date|2009|2|8|df=yes}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 8 February 2009\n| studio     =\n| venue      = [[Staples Center|The Staples Center]], [[Los Angeles]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{Duration|m=11|s=10}}\n| label      =\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Chris Martin]]|[[Jonny Buckland]]|[[Guy Berryman]]|[[Will Champion]]|[[Jay-Z]]}}\n| producer   =\n| chronology = [[Coldplay]]\n| prev_title = [[Life in Technicolor II]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Strawberry Swing]]\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Jay-Z]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Jockin' Jay-Z (Dope Boy Fresh)]]\n | prev_year  = 2008\n | title      = Lost+ / Viva la Vida (Live at the 51st Annual Grammy Awards)\n | year       = 2009\n | next_title = [[D.O.A. (Death of Auto-Tune)]]\n | next_year  = 2009\n}}\n}}\nThe song and \"[[Lost!|Lost+]]\" were performed live at the [[51st Annual Grammy Awards]], which took place at the [[Staples Center]] in [[Los Angeles]], on February 8, 2009. Coldplay performed a medley of \"Lost+\" and \"Viva la Vida\" at the ceremony. American rapper, [[Jay-Z]], who was the guest vocalist on \"Lost+\", performed \"Lost+\" with Coldplay on stage.\n\nThe performance was recorded and released on 8 February 2009, after the release of \"[[Life in Technicolor II]]\"\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = [[Lost!|Lost+]] (featuring [[Jay-Z]]) / Viva la Vida (Live At the [[51st Annual Grammy Awards]])\n|title1  = Lost+ <small>(featuring Jay-Z)</small> / Viva la Vida\n|length1 = 5:35\n|title2  = Lost+ <small>(featuring Jay-Z)</small> / Viva la Vida\n|note2   = Video\n|length2 =5:35\n}}\n\n==Cover versions==\n\n===Darin version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Viva la Vida\n| cover      = Viva-la-vida-darin.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Darin (singer)|Darin Zanyar]]\n| album      = [[Lovekiller (album)|Lovekiller]]\n| released   = October 2009\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   = 2009\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=4|s=36}}\n| label      = UNI\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Guy Berryman]]|[[Jonny Buckland]]|[[Will Champion]]|[[Chris Martin]]}}\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = Karma\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[You're Out of My Life]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\nSwedish singer [[Darin (singer)|Darin]]'s cover of the song reached number 1 on 30 October 2009 on the [[Sverigetopplistan|Swedish Singles Chart]].<ref>[http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Darin&titel=Viva+La+Vida&cat=s Darin's Viva la vida on swecharts.com] retrieved on 14 November 2009.</ref> The song appears in Darin's 2010 album ''[[Lovekiller (album)|Lovekiller]]''.\n\nIn 2010, it was yet again included as the B-side of Darin's \"[[You're Out of My Life (Darin song)|You're Out of My Life]]\" single, reaching #3 in the [[Sverigetopplistan|Swedish Singles Chart]].\n\nColdplay's original single had already charted in Sweden for a total of 49 weeks between 15 May 2008 and 23 October 2009, peaking at number seven.<ref>[http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Coldplay&titel=Viva+la+vida&cat=s Coldplay's Viva la vida on swecharts.com] retrieved on 14 November 2009.</ref>\n\n===Other versions===\n* [[2Cellos]] performed an instrumental cover of \"Viva la Vida\" in their debut album ''2Cellos''.\n* [[Weezer]] included their cover version of the song on the deluxe edition of their 2010 album ''[[Hurley (album)|Hurley]]''.\n* [[Electropop]] artist [[Joy Electric]] covered the song on the 2009 album ''[[Favorites at Play]]''.\n* Canadian band [[The Abrams Brothers]] covered \"Viva la Vida\" on the album ''Northern Redemption''.\n* Australian singer [[Mark Vincent]] recorded a version for his 2013 album ''[[The Quartet Sessions]]''\n* [[Scott Bradlee]]'s Postmodern Jukebox recorded a cover on YouTube and on the album ''Top Hat on Fleek'', with [[Puddles Pity Party]] as the lead vocalist.\n* Pet Shop Boys performed the song live on their 2009 Pandemonium Tour and the song appeared on their [[Christmas (Pet Shop Boys EP)|Christmas EP]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.petshopboys.co.uk/product/singles |title=Pet Shop Boys \u2014 Product \u2014 Christmas |publisher=Petshopboys.co.uk |accessdate=2010-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100509171055/http://www.petshopboys.co.uk/product/singles |archive-date=9 May 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* DJ Jonathan Hussein included a Trance remix version of \"Viva la Vida\" under the pseudonym \"Trance Winter\" in their album ''I'm Here'' in 2016.\n* German violinist David Garrett recorded a cover of Viva la Vida, made with a loop station, included on his 2012 album \"Music\".\n* Famous Minecraft Youtuber [[CaptainSparklez]] released a Parody of this song on his YouTube channel titled Fallen Kingdom.\n* Rapper [[Shawty Lo]] sampled \"Viva la Vida\" in his 2009 song \"Roll the Dice\", which was released to celebrate the ending of his feud with fellow rapper [[T.I.]] over the prior year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theboombox.com/shawty-lo-8-essential-tracks/|title=Remembering Shawty Lo: 8 Essential Tracks|date=21 September 2017|publisher=The BoomBox|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n* Boy band supergroup [[NKOTBSB]] performed a medley of their songs \"[[Single (New Kids on the Block song)|Single]]\" and \"[[The One (Backstreet Boys song)|The One]]\" over the instrumentation of \"Viva la Vida\" to open each of their concerts during their [[NKOTBSB Tour|2011-12 tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/07/concert_review_nkotbsb_arent_k.html|title=Concert review: New Kids on the Block and the Backstreet Boys aren't kids or boys anymore|date=31 July 2011|publisher=Penn State Patriot News|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n* Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] sampled \"Viva La Vida\" in his song \"Congratulations\" from his 2009 mixtape \"[[So Far Gone (mixtape)|So Far Gone]]\".\n\n==In popular culture==\n* Coldplay performed the song at the [[2012 Summer Paralympics closing ceremony]] (the ceremony to mark the end of the [[Paralympic Games]], and so also the end of the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] and [[2012 Summer Paralympics]]).\n* The song was performed simultaneously by amateur musicians across the UK on 9 September 2012 as part of the [[Bandstand Marathon]], the finale event of the [[2012 Cultural Olympiad]].\n* It was the last song played by [[Chris Moyles]] on his final [[Chris Moyles Show|BBC Radio 1 breakfast show]] on Friday 14 September 2012, the longest-running breakfast show in BBC Radio 1's history.\n* Coldplay performed some of the song live in ''[[The Simpsons]]'' episode \"[[Million Dollar Maybe]]\".<ref>{{cite AV media|url=http://vimeo.com/9062866|title=Coldplay on the Simpsons|date=29 January 2010|publisher=[[Vimeo]]|people=[[Coldplay]]}}</ref>\n* The song was used in the official soundtrack for ''[[The Big Year]]''.\n* The song was played to the crew of the [[Space Shuttle Atlantis]] to wake them up on day two of [[STS-135]], the final mission of the Space Shuttle program. It was played for crew member [[Douglas G. Hurley|Douglas Hurley]].\n* The song was used as a [[fanfare]] to welcome the [[Singapore Armed Forces Parachute Team]] (better known as the ''Red Lions'') during the National Day Celebrations of 2011 in [[Singapore]].\n* The song was used by the Dutch [[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]] (VVD) when Party Leader and Prime Minister Mark Rutte walked on stage to present his acceptance speech after winning the 2012 parliamentary elections.\n* The song also appears on ''[[NBA 2K13]]'' as part of the game's soundtrack.\n* \"Viva la Vida\" has also been spoofed in a music video titled \"Fallen Kingdom\", created by YouTubers [[Jordan Maron|CaptainSparklez]] and TryHardNinja, in the style of the popular videogame Minecraft.\n* This song has since been used as the main theme of Indonesian television channel [[Antv|ANTV]], as part of the channel's 20th anniversary.\n* As of 8 October 2011, the song has been made available for download in ''[[Rock Band 3]]'' as by itself or as part of the \"Coldplay Collection 1\" track pack. \n* The song was played in a montage for [[Jerry Lewis]] in his work to receive the [[Jean Hersholt Humanitarian Award]] at the [[81st Academy Awards]].\n* The song was played in honor of [[Markus N\u00e4slund]] for his [[Vancouver Canucks]] jersey retirement ceremony on 11 December 2010. The song was played in the video tribute for N\u00e4slund.\n* \"Viva la Vida\" was used as [[FC Barcelona]]'s season ending song of their historic [[2008\u201309 FC Barcelona season]] as they won all six major trophies in European football league.\n* The song was played in honor of retiring [[Phil Taylor (darts player)|Phil Taylor]] after the [[2018 PDC World Darts Championship]] final against [[Rob Cross (darts player)|Rob Cross]]\n* The song was played at the conclusion of the [[series finale]] of the television show [[Suits (American TV series)|Suits]], \"One Last Con.\"\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2008\u201309)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|2|artist=Coldplay|song=Viva la vida}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|6|artist=Coldplay|song=Viva la vida}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|4|artist=Coldplay|song=Viva la vida}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|7|artist=Coldplay|song=Viva la vida}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|4|artist=Coldplay|song=Viva la vida|artistid=401639}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Czech Republic|1|year=2008|week=44}}\n|-\n{{singlec